<subSubSection id="DC9170A2294F0970FFE04EF0FE1BFBD9" pageId="20" pageNumber="1064" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="94342329294F0970FFE04EF0FE1BFBD9" blockId="20.[163,780,938,1052]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1064">
<emphasis id="A6FFFF3B294F0970FFE04EF0FEC7FC7A" box="[163,289,938,959]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="1064">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name is derived from the Latin 
<taxonomicName id="538B58AA294F0970FDFF4EF1FCE3FC05" box="[700,773,939,960]" class="Lobosa" family="Arcellidae" genus="Galeripora" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Arcellinida" pageId="20" pageNumber="1064" phylum="Amoebozoa" rank="species" species="sitiens">
<emphasis id="A6FFFF3B294F0970FDFF4EF1FCE3FC05" box="[700,773,939,960]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="1064">sitiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, dry or thirsty. We propose this name because the habitat of this species is characterized by prolonged drought with episodic rainfall.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
